WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.481
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

00:12.882 --> 00:15.885
-♪ SOME PEOPLE STAND
IN THE DARKNESS ♪

00:17.017 --> 00:20.585
♪ AFRAID TO STEP
INTO THE LIGHT ♪

00:20.716 --> 00:24.633
♪ SOME PEOPLE NEED
TO HAVE SOMEBODY ♪

00:24.763 --> 00:28.028
♪ WHEN THE EDGE OF
SURRENDER'S IN SIGHT ♪

00:28.158 --> 00:34.077
♪ DON'T YOU WORRY,
IT'S GONNA BE ALRIGHT ♪

00:36.949 --> 00:38.821
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

00:38.951 --> 00:42.303
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

00:45.523 --> 00:49.353
♪ [I'LL BE READY]
I'LL BE READY ♪

00:49.484 --> 00:53.357
♪ [WHENEVER YOU FEAR]
NO, DON'T YOU FEAR ♪

00:53.488 --> 00:56.273
♪ I'LL BE READY

00:56.839 --> 01:02.845
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS,
I'M ALWAYS HERE ♪

01:20.732 --> 01:22.778
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

01:22.908 --> 01:26.086
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

01:29.567 --> 01:33.571
♪ [I'LL BE READY]
I'LL BE READY ♪

01:33.702 --> 01:37.401
♪ [WHENEVER YOU FEAR]
NO, DON'T YOU FEAR ♪

01:37.532 --> 01:40.143
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:40.839 --> 01:46.758
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS,
I'M ALWAYS HERE ♪

02:01.686 --> 02:06.778
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

02:07.475 --> 02:09.651
-HELP! THERE'S A SHARK OUT HERE!

02:10.390 --> 02:11.609
IT WAS HUGE.

02:13.394 --> 02:14.264
-MATT: HELP HIM UP.

02:14.395 --> 02:15.439
GET HIM UP, SUMMER.

02:15.570 --> 02:21.097
[SUSPENSEFUL VIOLIN MUSIC]

02:21.228 --> 02:24.492
-MATT, HURRY UP, THERE'S
A SHARK COMING RIGHT AT YOU.

02:30.062 --> 02:31.151
[SCREAMING]

02:31.281 --> 02:32.413
MATT!

02:35.024 --> 02:36.939
MATT!
-SUMMER, HELP!

02:39.637 --> 02:42.597
-MATT!
-SUMMER!

02:45.687 --> 02:48.559
HELP ME!

02:48.690 --> 02:49.865
-SUMMER: MATT!

02:50.909 --> 02:53.999
[PANTING]

02:57.481 --> 02:59.614
-MATT: I'VE BEEN HAVING
THESE NIGHTMARES ABOUT SHARKS.

03:00.963 --> 03:03.661
IT'S CRAZY, I'VE NEVER
BEEN AFRAID OF SHARKS.

03:03.792 --> 03:05.576
-WELL, MAYBE THOSE SIGHTINGS

03:05.707 --> 03:07.143
OFF OF POINT DUMAS
RE-TRIGGERED THEM.

03:07.274 --> 03:10.886
-NO, THEY STARTED BEFORE THAT.

03:11.974 --> 03:13.976
I HAVEN'T HAD A FULL
NIGHT'S SLEEP IN A MONTH.

03:14.106 --> 03:15.978
-MATT, WHY DIDN'T YOU
SAY SOMETHING SOONER?

03:17.806 --> 03:18.894
-I THOUGHT THEY WOULD STOP.

03:20.112 --> 03:21.723
BUT INSTEAD, THEY'RE
GETTING WORSE.

03:23.725 --> 03:25.161
LAST NIGHT, THE SHARK
ACTUALLY GOT ME.

03:27.337 --> 03:30.862
YOU TRIED TO HELP,
BUT YOU COULDN'T.

03:37.347 --> 03:42.352
[HUSTLE AND BUSTLE]

03:44.354 --> 03:46.661
-GWEN, YOU ONLY
HAVE ONE PROBLEM,

03:47.618 --> 03:48.663
YOU'RE A TOTAL MESS.

03:50.099 --> 03:51.100
YOU DON'T KNOW HOW TO DRESS,

03:52.188 --> 03:54.408
YOU NEVER DO ANYTHING
WITH YOUR HAIR.

03:54.538 --> 03:56.236
YOU JUST DON'T SEEM TO CARE.

04:00.675 --> 04:02.807
-GWEN: OF COURSE
I CARE, MATTIE.

04:04.156 --> 04:05.767
WHY DO YOU HAVE TO BE SO MEAN?

04:06.681 --> 04:08.248
-I'M YOUR SISTER, GWEN.

04:08.378 --> 04:11.512
NO ONE IS GOING TO BE
THIS HONEST WITH YOU.

04:12.861 --> 04:14.254
OH, GWEN.

04:15.603 --> 04:18.040
GWEN, YOU'RE NEVER
GOING TO GET A MAN

04:18.170 --> 04:19.563
THE WAY THAT YOU ARE.

04:33.098 --> 04:34.839
-I'LL SHOW YOU, SISTER DEAR.

04:35.536 --> 04:37.799
YOU'RE NOT THE ONLY
ONE WHO CAN GET A MAN.

04:41.672 --> 04:46.677
[EERIE PIANO MUSIC]

05:43.343 --> 05:44.344
EXCUSE ME?

05:45.083 --> 05:45.997
-YEAH?

05:46.520 --> 05:49.044
-I WONDERED
IF YOU COULD TELL ME

05:49.174 --> 05:51.742
WHAT THAT FLAG MEANS.

05:52.395 --> 05:53.875
-WELL, IT'S A WARNING FLAG.

05:54.005 --> 05:55.703
IT MEANS THERE'S
A DANGEROUS RIP TODAY.

05:57.444 --> 05:58.793
BE CAREFUL.

05:59.446 --> 06:01.448
-WELL, THEN I THINK I'LL JUST
STICK RIGHT HERE ON THE SAND,

06:01.578 --> 06:03.406
BECAUSE I'M NOT
A VERY GOOD SWIMMER.

06:03.928 --> 06:05.321
-OKAY.

06:07.671 --> 06:08.716
-MY NAME IS GWEN.

06:09.543 --> 06:10.370
-WHAT?

06:11.762 --> 06:14.025
-NOTHING, JUST I'M GWEN,
THAT'S ALL.

06:14.156 --> 06:16.941
-OH, THAT'S SHORT
FOR GUINEVERE, RIGHT?

06:18.116 --> 06:19.814
WELL, GUINEVERE,
BE SURE YOU PUT ON

06:19.944 --> 06:21.163
PLENTY OF SUNBLOCK TODAY.

06:21.293 --> 06:22.512
DON'T WANNA GET YOU SUNBURNED.

06:25.297 --> 06:30.781
[MYSTERIOUS WOODWIND MUSIC]

06:44.447 --> 06:46.231
-CHEERS.
HERE'S TO A GREAT VACATION.

06:46.362 --> 06:47.711
-CHEERS, BABY.
[LAUGHING]

06:51.411 --> 06:56.198
[WHISTLING]

07:18.568 --> 07:19.569
-WOMAN: HI.

07:23.747 --> 07:25.836
-I'M GONNA HAVE TO ASK
YOU TO PUT THE BEER AWAY.

07:26.402 --> 07:27.925
-WHY? WE'RE NOT GOING SWIMMING.

07:28.056 --> 07:29.666
-WE ARE OVER 21.

07:30.232 --> 07:31.494
-DO YOU WANT TO SEE OUR IDS?

07:32.147 --> 07:33.975
-I'M NOT A BARTENDER,
I'M A LIFEGUARD,

07:34.105 --> 07:34.932
AND I'VE GOT A JOB TO DO.

07:35.063 --> 07:36.630
-OKAY, WE'LL PUT THEM AWAY.

07:41.112 --> 07:42.026
-THANK YOU.

07:45.813 --> 07:49.294
-MAN: HELP!
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

07:49.425 --> 07:50.905
HELP ME!

07:54.343 --> 07:55.649
HELP!

07:57.172 --> 07:57.999
HELP!

08:00.392 --> 08:01.829
PLEASE HELP ME!

08:09.097 --> 08:10.315
HELP!

08:14.232 --> 08:16.496
-HELP!
-HELP US!

08:19.455 --> 08:20.369
HELP!

08:20.500 --> 08:21.762
HELP ME!

08:42.783 --> 08:45.873
[SCREAMING]

08:50.138 --> 08:51.661
-OKAY.
-HELP!

08:56.797 --> 08:58.407
-I GOTCHA, RELAX.

09:00.322 --> 09:03.847
[TRIUMPHANT ORCHESTRAL MUSIC]

09:36.271 --> 09:37.185
COUGH IT UP, COME ON.

09:38.534 --> 09:40.928
[COUGHING]
-YOU'LL BE ALRIGHT.

09:41.885 --> 09:42.930
-HE'S ALRIGHT.

09:44.584 --> 09:48.152
-BREATHE, YOU JUST GOTTA
LIE HERE A MINUTE.

09:51.329 --> 09:52.504
-HERE'S YOUR GLASSES.

09:53.114 --> 09:54.681
-THANK YOU, LADY GUINEVERE.

09:54.811 --> 09:56.465
-THAT WAS THE MOST AMAZING
THING I'VE EVER SEEN.

09:56.596 --> 09:58.162
YOU SAVED THEIR LIVES.

09:58.772 --> 10:00.164
-WELL, THEY WEREN'T
AS SMART AS YOU.

10:00.295 --> 10:01.688
THEY DIDN'T ASK WHAT
THAT FLAG MEANT.

10:01.818 --> 10:03.211
-BUT YOU, YOU
MADE A DIFFERENCE.

10:03.341 --> 10:04.952
IF YOU HADN'T BEEN THERE,
SHE'D BE DEAD.

10:05.474 --> 10:06.475
-"SHE"?

10:07.345 --> 10:10.174
-I MEAN HE, I MEAN
THEM. [STAMMERING]

10:10.697 --> 10:11.915
-IT'S OKAY.

10:12.046 --> 10:13.700
SO ARE YOU FROM OUT OF TOWN?
-MM-HMM.

10:14.352 --> 10:16.224
-MY SISTER AND I ARE
TRAVELING ACROSS COUNTRY

10:16.354 --> 10:17.181
IN OUR TRAILER, SEE?

10:18.443 --> 10:20.576
IT'S SOMETHING THAT WE'VE ALWAYS
WANTED TO DO TOGETHER.

10:20.707 --> 10:21.882
-A TRAILER?

10:22.578 --> 10:24.798
MUST BE PRETTY TIGHT TO SPEND
THAT MUCH TIME TOGETHER.

10:25.842 --> 10:27.583
-MY SISTER AND
I ARE VERY CLOSE.

10:29.237 --> 10:30.281
-WOW, THAT WAS REALLY GREAT.

10:30.412 --> 10:32.066
-YOU WERE INCREDIBLE OUT THERE.

10:32.196 --> 10:33.633
YOU'VE DONE YOUR
GOOD DEED FOR TODAY,
CAN WE GO NOW?

10:33.763 --> 10:35.547
-NO, GIRLS, LOOK,
I AM A LIFEGUARD.

10:35.678 --> 10:37.071
I'M ON DUTY. I CAN'T--
-YOU HAVE TO COME WITH US.

10:37.201 --> 10:38.159
-I CAN'T COME WITH YOU.

10:39.116 --> 10:41.423
I'M A LIFEGUARD,
I'M ON DUTY, SO LEAVE IT.

10:41.553 --> 10:44.034
[GROANING]

10:50.562 --> 10:53.783
[SAUCY SAXOPHONE MUSIC]

11:27.121 --> 11:27.948
-OH, YOU'RE CLOSING UP?

11:28.078 --> 11:29.340
I HAD MY HEART SET ON A SWIM.

11:30.298 --> 11:31.821
-WELL, I WOULDN'T RECOMMEND IT.

11:31.952 --> 11:33.997
THE SANTA ANAS ARE BRINGING
IN A PRETTY BIG SWELL.

11:34.650 --> 11:36.043
THE RIPS ARE GONNA
BE PRETTY HEAVY.

11:36.608 --> 11:37.784
-WHAT WOULD YOU RECOMMEND?

11:37.914 --> 11:39.829
I'M FROM OUT OF TOWN.

11:40.700 --> 11:42.092
-THAT DEPENDS ON
WHAT YOU LIKE TO DO.

11:42.223 --> 11:44.181
-I LIKE TO MEET NEW PEOPLE.

11:45.792 --> 11:47.054
MY NAME IS MATTIE BROWN.

11:47.184 --> 11:48.838
-I'M MITCH BUCHANNON.

11:50.231 --> 11:52.494
YOU WOULDN'T HAPPEN TO HAVE
A SISTER NAMED GWEN, WOULD YOU?

11:52.624 --> 11:55.192
-YES, GWEN. HAVE YOU MET HER?

11:55.323 --> 11:57.412
-YEAH, EARLIER TODAY.

11:57.934 --> 11:58.979
SHE SAID YOU TWO ARE
TRAVELING AROUND THE COUNTRY

11:59.109 --> 11:59.719
IN A TRAILER.

12:00.589 --> 12:01.938
SOUNDS LIKE FUN.

12:02.069 --> 12:03.940
-WOULD BE IF GWEN
WASN'T SUCH A DRAG.

12:04.854 --> 12:06.856
I CAN'T BELIEVE I'M STUCK
ON THIS WHOLE TRIP WITH HER.

12:08.292 --> 12:12.427
LISTEN, WHY DON'T YOU
COME BY OUR TRAILER

12:12.557 --> 12:14.298
WHEN YOU'VE FINISHED
WHATEVER YOU HAVE TO DO HERE?

12:14.864 --> 12:16.039
-NO, I DON'T THINK SO.

12:16.170 --> 12:19.129
-PLEASE? WE'LL COOK YOU DINNER.

12:19.695 --> 12:21.392
IT WOULD MAKE GWEN'S WHOLE TRIP

12:21.523 --> 12:22.916
TO HAVE SOMEONE LIKE YOU
COME AND HAVE DINNER WITH US.

12:24.308 --> 12:27.050
-SOUNDS GREAT,
BUT I'VE GOT PLANS TONIGHT.

12:27.181 --> 12:28.225
-TOMORROW NIGHT, THEN.

12:30.488 --> 12:31.925
PLEASE?

12:32.577 --> 12:33.970
IT'LL BE FUN, I PROMISE.

12:35.058 --> 12:37.321
WE'RE STRANGERS
FROM A STRANGE LAND,

12:37.800 --> 12:40.107
AND YOU CAN TELL US WHAT
WE CAN SEE AND DO HERE.

12:41.282 --> 12:42.674
-OKAY.

12:42.805 --> 12:45.025
-GREAT, THAT'S OUR
TRAILER OVER THERE.

12:45.590 --> 12:46.853
-ALRIGHT, I'LL SEE YOU
THERE TOMORROW NIGHT.

12:46.983 --> 12:48.985
-MAYBE BEFORE,
ARE YOU HERE TOMORROW?

12:49.116 --> 12:49.943
-I'LL BE HERE.

12:50.073 --> 12:51.945
-THEN SO WILL I.

12:52.554 --> 12:55.600
-WELL, HAVE A NICE NIGHT,

12:55.731 --> 12:58.342
AND SAY HI TO GUINEVERE FOR ME.

13:10.180 --> 13:11.355
-MATT.

13:13.227 --> 13:16.099
C.J. TELLS ME YOU'RE GOING
DIVING IN A SHARK CAGE.

13:16.708 --> 13:18.362
-DON'T TRY TO TALK ME
OUT OF THIS, SUMMER.

13:18.493 --> 13:20.364
THE ONLY WAY I'M GONNA
STOP THESE NIGHTMARES

13:20.495 --> 13:21.801
IS IF I FACE MY FEAR.

13:22.802 --> 13:24.412
-WELL, THEN I AM GOING WITH YOU.

13:24.542 --> 13:27.415
-SUMMER, I HAVE
TO DO THIS ALONE.

13:29.025 --> 13:30.418
-NO, YOU DON'T, MATT.

13:30.984 --> 13:32.333
LOOK, I'M HERE FOR YOU.

13:32.463 --> 13:33.421
I COULDN'T HELP YOU
IN YOUR NIGHTMARE,

13:33.551 --> 13:35.118
BUT I CAN HELP YOU NOW.

13:37.686 --> 13:39.862
-OKAY. COME ON.

13:50.786 --> 13:52.309
-SUMMER:
DO YOU HAVE TO DO THAT?

13:52.832 --> 13:54.224
-YOU WANNA SEE
SHARKS, DON'T YA?

13:56.836 --> 14:00.665
[SERIOUS VIOLIN MUSIC]

14:02.537 --> 14:03.755
-LET'S GET ON WITH THIS.

14:05.018 --> 14:05.627
-YOU'RE THE BOSS.

14:09.761 --> 14:10.719
BE CAREFUL.

14:11.198 --> 14:15.593
[SUSPENSEFUL ORCHESTRAL MUSIC]

15:14.783 --> 15:17.917
[MENACING MUSIC]

15:27.317 --> 15:28.014
-MATT!

15:29.754 --> 15:31.495
GRAB THE ROPE, HE'S DRIFTING!

15:31.626 --> 15:32.932
HELP ME GRAB THE ROPE!

15:37.327 --> 15:38.676
[GASPS] NO.

15:39.416 --> 15:42.071
[INTENSE ORCHESTRAL MUSIC]

16:03.397 --> 16:04.876
GET ME OUT!

16:07.227 --> 16:09.969
HELP ME! GET ME OUT OF HERE!

16:20.240 --> 16:21.981
HELP ME!

16:26.333 --> 16:27.638
MATT!

16:30.902 --> 16:33.209
[GASPS]

16:38.171 --> 16:43.002
[SOMBER WOODWIND MUSIC]

16:46.135 --> 16:47.136
-HEY, MATT.

16:53.664 --> 16:54.839
HEY, WHAT'S WRONG?

16:56.015 --> 16:57.190
-I HAD ANOTHER NIGHTMARE.

16:57.929 --> 16:59.105
LAST NIGHT WAS THE WORST ONE.

16:59.583 --> 17:00.802
-WHAT HAPPENED?

17:02.325 --> 17:03.892
-I WAS IN THE SHARK CAGE,

17:04.935 --> 17:05.894
YOU WERE THERE ON A BOAT,

17:07.503 --> 17:08.853
AND YOU FELL INTO THE WATER.

17:09.419 --> 17:10.898
I TRIED TO GET YOU BUT I--

17:11.030 --> 17:13.641
-SO, THIS TIME A SHARK
ATTACKED ME, RIGHT?

17:15.991 --> 17:17.384
-I COULDN'T GET
OUT OF THE CAGE.

17:18.385 --> 17:20.256
-IT'S NOT ABOUT SHARKS, MATT.

17:20.821 --> 17:22.476
THESE NIGHTMARES ARE ABOUT US.

17:22.606 --> 17:24.304
-US? WHAT ARE
YOU TALKING ABOUT?

17:24.434 --> 17:25.305
-OUR RELATIONSHIP.

17:25.435 --> 17:26.132
-SUMMER--

17:26.262 --> 17:28.395
-YOU FEEL TRAPPED, CAGED.

17:28.525 --> 17:30.136
-I DO NOT.

17:30.266 --> 17:32.138
-MATT, BEING WITH ME IS
WHAT IS FRIGHTENING YOU.

17:33.617 --> 17:34.444
-THAT'S CRAZY.

17:34.575 --> 17:37.230
-MATT, THESE NIGHTMARES BEGAN

17:37.360 --> 17:39.145
AS SOON AS WE STARTED
GETTING SERIOUS.

17:39.275 --> 17:42.191
LOOK AT THE SYMBOLISM,
IT'S OBVIOUS.

17:42.322 --> 17:44.324
YOU'RE AFRAID TO MAKE
A COMMITMENT TO ME.

17:46.761 --> 17:50.286
[DOWNCAST MUSIC]

18:03.995 --> 18:05.606
-GWEN: IT'S NOT FAIR, MATTIE.

18:05.736 --> 18:08.087
I SAW MITCH FIRST, HE LIKES ME.

18:08.217 --> 18:10.567
HE CALLED ME LADY GUINEVERE.

18:10.698 --> 18:13.179
-MATTIE: WELL, IT DOESN'T
MATTER WHAT HE CALLED YOU,

18:13.309 --> 18:16.225
BECAUSE HE'S COMING
HERE TO BE WITH ME.

18:16.356 --> 18:19.837
BECAUSE I'M PRETTY AND BECAUSE
I'M EXCITING TO BE WITH.

18:19.968 --> 18:24.015
-LOOK, I MIGHT NOT BE GLAMOROUS

18:24.146 --> 18:26.279
AND EXCITING LIKE YOU, MATTIE.

18:27.106 --> 18:30.109
BUT THAT DOESN'T MEAN THAT
I SHOULDN'T BE HERE, TOO.

18:34.243 --> 18:39.248
[MYSTERIOUS PIANO MUSIC]

18:43.774 --> 18:49.171
ONE LOOK AT YOU, GWEN,
AND HE'D LEAVE.

18:50.738 --> 18:51.956
YOU'RE PATHETIC!

18:53.262 --> 18:56.047
I DON'T WANT TO HEAR YOU
AND I DON'T WANT TO SEE YOU!

18:58.876 --> 19:02.576
[SOBBING]

19:05.535 --> 19:08.756
YOU ALWAYS TAKE
EVERYTHING AWAY FROM ME.

19:10.584 --> 19:12.412
EVERYTHING,

19:14.675 --> 19:17.112
EVEN MAMA'S LOVE.

19:20.942 --> 19:24.163
DON'T YOU START SOBBING!
DO YOU HEAR ME?

19:29.429 --> 19:33.824
I HATE YOU! YOU ARE SO WEAK!

19:41.702 --> 19:43.225
I'M GONNA GET MITCH.

19:45.532 --> 19:49.710
MITCH IS GONNA BE MINE,
ALL MINE.

19:51.886 --> 19:53.931
AND YOU'D BETTER NOT INTERFERE.

19:55.672 --> 19:59.198
[SOBBING]

20:00.024 --> 20:03.289
YOU'RE THE ONE
WHO'S INTERFERING, MATTIE.

20:05.769 --> 20:07.423
YEAH, YOU ARE.

20:09.817 --> 20:11.340
BUT I'M GONNA STOP YOU.

20:12.733 --> 20:14.952
I'M GONNA STOP YOU THIS TIME.

20:26.790 --> 20:30.229
[SINISTER ORCHESTRAL MUSIC]

20:31.708 --> 20:33.144
[WINCING]
OW.

20:45.461 --> 20:47.289
-MORNING THERE,
MY LADY, HOW ARE YA?

20:47.420 --> 20:50.684
-WELL, I THOUGHT
MAYBE YOU WOULD HAVE SOMETHING

20:50.814 --> 20:52.207
TO PUT ON THIS.
-OOH.

20:52.338 --> 20:53.469
-I FELL ON THE ROCKS.

20:54.644 --> 20:56.559
-THAT'S NASTY, COME ON,
COME ON, I'LL HELP YOU OUT.

20:59.127 --> 21:01.912
TELL YOU WHAT.
WHY DON'T YOU JUMP IN THE CHAIR
AND PUT YOUR LEG UP?

21:02.783 --> 21:03.871
I'LL FIX THAT UP IN A JIFFY.

21:11.008 --> 21:13.576
OKAY, OKAY.

21:13.707 --> 21:16.579
NOW, THIS IS GONNA STING
A LITTLE BIT, ALRIGHT?

21:25.719 --> 21:26.415
THERE YOU GO.

21:27.416 --> 21:28.983
YOU KNOW, YOUR SISTER
MATTIE CAME BY, YESTERDAY,

21:29.113 --> 21:29.984
AND INVITED ME TO DINNER.

21:30.114 --> 21:31.420
IS THAT STILL HAPPENING?

21:32.291 --> 21:33.901
-YES, BUT MATTIE
WON'T BE THERE.

21:34.902 --> 21:36.164
-NO?

21:37.208 --> 21:38.732
-WELL, SHE MAY COME LATE.

21:38.862 --> 21:40.560
SHE STILL WANTED YOU TO COME.

21:41.343 --> 21:42.736
YOU'LL COME STILL, RIGHT?

21:42.866 --> 21:44.259
I MEAN, WE COOKED
DINNER AND EVERYTHING.

21:44.390 --> 21:45.434
-SURE, I WOULDN'T MISS IT.

21:45.565 --> 21:46.827
BELIEVE ME, I'M STARVED.

21:49.699 --> 21:50.613
OKAY, THAT SHOULD DO IT.

21:54.878 --> 21:57.881
-WELL, I'D BETTER GO
AND GET EVERYTHING READY.

21:58.447 --> 22:00.057
AN HOUR OKAY?

22:00.188 --> 22:02.233
-HOUR'S FINE, ALL I GOTTA
DO IS CHANGE AND SHOWER.

22:03.104 --> 22:04.497
ALRIGHT?
-OKAY.

22:04.627 --> 22:06.063
-OKAY. SEE YA.

22:13.593 --> 22:14.811
BYE, THANK YOU.

22:14.942 --> 22:16.117
-BYE-BYE, SEE YA.

22:22.210 --> 22:26.257
[THUNDERING]

22:34.353 --> 22:38.400
[MYSTERIOUS PIANO MUSIC]

23:25.665 --> 23:26.622
[DOOR KNOCKING]

23:26.753 --> 23:28.319
-COMING, JUST A MINUTE.

23:37.851 --> 23:39.287
HI, COME ON IN.

23:39.418 --> 23:40.810
-THANKS.

23:40.941 --> 23:43.030
-LET ME TAKE YOUR JACKET
FOR YOU. YOU'RE SO WET.

23:44.553 --> 23:46.337
-THEY SAY IT NEVER RAINS
IN SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA.

23:46.468 --> 23:48.078
-I LOVE THE RAIN,

23:48.209 --> 23:50.472
ESPECIALLY WHEN IT'S
WARM AND COZY INSIDE.

23:52.039 --> 23:53.170
HI.
-HI.

23:54.171 --> 23:55.564
-GWEN COULDN'T MAKE IT TONIGHT.

23:56.347 --> 23:59.176
-OH, WELL, GWEN TOLD ME
YOU COULDN'T MAKE IT.

23:59.699 --> 24:01.352
-WHEN IT COMES TO
ENTERTAINING MEN,

24:01.875 --> 24:03.224
GWEN IS A BASKET CASE.

24:05.661 --> 24:07.184
I HOPE YOU LIKE LAMB CHOPS.

24:07.315 --> 24:08.664
-WELL, I DON'T
EAT MUCH RED MEAT,

24:08.795 --> 24:12.146
BUT I LOVE LAMB CHOPS.

24:12.276 --> 24:15.454
-GOOD, I'M GLAD YOU CAME.

24:16.846 --> 24:17.891
WHY DON'T WE HAVE A DRINK?

24:18.979 --> 24:20.459
-BEFORE DINNER, HM?
-SURE.

24:20.589 --> 24:22.852
-I HOPE YOU LIKE RED WINE.
-YEAH.

24:22.983 --> 24:24.375
-YOU DO? GOOD.

24:24.898 --> 24:26.073
-IT'S REALLY COMING DOWN.

24:26.203 --> 24:28.292
-I KNOW, I LOVE IT.

24:30.773 --> 24:31.905
THERE YOU GO.

24:35.386 --> 24:37.476
TO DREAMS COMING TRUE.

24:38.477 --> 24:39.826
-CHEERS.
-CHEERS.

24:41.262 --> 24:44.178
[THUNDERING]

24:48.574 --> 24:49.836
WHY DON'T YOU SIT DOWN?

24:49.966 --> 24:51.968
SIT DOWN, AND I'LL
FIX DINNER UP.

24:52.099 --> 24:56.190
JUST SIT DOWN, RELAX,
ENJOY YOUR WINE, OKAY?

24:56.320 --> 24:57.757
-OKAY, THANKS.

25:02.370 --> 25:04.807
-I WAS THINKING
THAT AFTER DINNER,

25:05.460 --> 25:10.378
I COULD TURN ON SOME MUSIC
AND THAT WE COULD DANCE.

25:11.466 --> 25:13.120
I LOVE TO DANCE.

25:15.296 --> 25:16.558
DO YOU LIKE TO DANCE?

25:18.342 --> 25:19.953
-YEAH, SOMETIMES.

25:22.782 --> 25:25.132
ARE YOU SURE GWEN'S NOT GONNA
BE UPSET ABOUT ALL THIS?

25:25.262 --> 25:26.916
-WHEN ISN'T GWEN UPSET?

25:29.397 --> 25:31.878
GWEN DOESN'T KNOW HOW
TO HAVE A GOOD TIME.

25:33.357 --> 25:35.490
BUT ENOUGH ABOUT GWEN, YOU KNOW?

25:36.273 --> 25:37.536
TONIGHT IS ABOUT US.

25:43.933 --> 25:45.326
TO NEW FRIENDS.

25:47.415 --> 25:51.419
[SENSUAL SAXOPHONE MUSIC]

25:58.905 --> 26:00.602
-I'M NOT MUCH OF
A DRINKER, BUT--

26:06.869 --> 26:08.436
-JUST RELAX, MITCH.

26:09.263 --> 26:11.134
ENJOY THE WINE.
SEE, YOU'RE FINE.

26:13.789 --> 26:17.924
[EERIE PIANO MUSIC]

26:23.930 --> 26:25.801
-GWEN'S VOICE:
DON'T DO IT, MATTIE.

26:26.715 --> 26:28.456
DON'T TAKE HIM THERE.

26:28.978 --> 26:30.414
-MATTIE: SHUT UP.

26:31.415 --> 26:33.330
YOU NEVER KNOW WHAT TO DO.

26:39.772 --> 26:43.384
[MYSTERIOUS ORCHESTRAL MUSIC]

27:06.842 --> 27:08.365
-GWEN'S VOICE:
IT'S CONDEMNED, MATTIE.

27:08.496 --> 27:10.498
THAT PLACE IS DANGEROUS,
PLEASE DON'T DO THIS.

27:11.586 --> 27:13.370
-MATTIE: YOU'RE WEAK, GWEN.

27:13.936 --> 27:15.721
THAT'S WHY YOU NEED ME.

27:15.851 --> 27:18.375
YOU'RE NOTHING WITHOUT ME.

27:20.073 --> 27:22.510
-GWEN'S VOICE: I DON'T WANT
YOU HERE, LEAVE ME ALONE.

27:25.600 --> 27:27.515
-MATTIE: I'M HERE, GWEN.

27:28.472 --> 27:32.128
I'M HERE TO STAY AND THERE'S
NOTHING YOU CAN DO ABOUT IT.

27:33.434 --> 27:35.392
[EVIL LAUGHTER]

27:49.363 --> 27:53.759
[SUSPICIOUS ORGAN MUSIC]

28:41.763 --> 28:43.112
-DON'T WORRY, MITCH,

28:44.374 --> 28:47.073
I'M GONNA TAKE SUCH
GOOD CARE OF YOU.

28:52.295 --> 28:55.472
WE'RE TOGETHER NOW
AND NO ONE IS GONNA BOTHER US.

28:55.603 --> 28:59.694
[SEDUCTIVE SAXOPHONE MUSIC]

29:22.325 --> 29:26.025
[CREEPY PIANO MUSIC]

29:39.516 --> 29:41.736
[GRUNTING]

29:44.652 --> 29:45.653
-WHAT THE HELL?

29:52.878 --> 29:54.270
HELP!

29:56.142 --> 29:59.232
HELP! HELP!

30:03.540 --> 30:08.067
HEY! HEY! HEY!
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?

30:08.197 --> 30:09.546
-GOOD MORNING.

30:12.854 --> 30:15.074
-WHERE AM I?
WHAT THE HELL'S GOING ON?

30:15.204 --> 30:16.510
-OH, I HOPE YOU SLEPT WELL.

30:22.037 --> 30:23.386
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

30:23.517 --> 30:25.475
-I MADE YOU SUCH
A WONDERFUL BREAKFAST.

30:26.607 --> 30:28.174
ARE YOU HUNGRY? YOU MUST BE.

30:28.304 --> 30:29.828
I'M GONNA PUT IT RIGHT HERE.

30:33.092 --> 30:36.051
-MATTIE, YOU GOTTA
GET ME OUT OF HERE.

30:36.182 --> 30:38.271
THE TIDE'S COMING IN.
THAT'S THE WATER LINE.

30:38.401 --> 30:40.360
I'LL DROWN, NOW YOU
GOTTA GET ME OUT OF HERE!

30:41.840 --> 30:44.277
-WHENEVER YOU'RE READY TO EAT,
YOU GO AHEAD, OKAY?

30:44.407 --> 30:45.408
-WHAT?

30:49.325 --> 30:51.066
HEY! HEY!

30:55.897 --> 30:58.030
HEY! HEY!

31:03.296 --> 31:06.386
-BARNETT: SET ONE BUOY HERE
AND THE OTHER 20 YARDS NORTH.

31:13.523 --> 31:15.221
-YOU SURE YOU WANT
TO GO IN THE WATER?

31:15.351 --> 31:16.918
THERE'S A SHARK OUT THERE.

31:17.484 --> 31:19.181
-I'M NOT AFRAID OF
SHARKS, REMEMBER?

31:19.703 --> 31:21.096
JUST RELATIONSHIPS.

31:42.378 --> 31:44.032
-BARNETT: OKAY, SUMMER. GO.

31:48.210 --> 31:49.864
-YOU DON'T HAVE TO WAIT,
WE'LL SWIM IN.

31:49.995 --> 31:51.387
-OKAY, BE CAREFUL.

32:02.442 --> 32:03.486
-MATT: DON'T GO ON!

32:05.619 --> 32:06.794
MOVE TO THE LEFT.

32:11.059 --> 32:14.671
[MENACING MUSIC]

32:33.342 --> 32:34.213
PERFECT.

32:45.485 --> 32:48.749
-MATT! MATT!

32:50.751 --> 32:52.144
-SUMMER!

32:52.535 --> 32:53.667
BARNETT!

32:55.930 --> 32:57.192
-MATT!

33:00.369 --> 33:01.370
-SUMMER!

33:15.384 --> 33:16.777
-MATT!

33:20.302 --> 33:22.304
-GET OUT OF THE WAY,
GET OUT OF THE WAY.

33:34.186 --> 33:35.535
-HELP ME.

33:36.057 --> 33:38.277
BARNETT, WE GOTTA GET MATT
OUT OF THERE, THERE'S A SHARK.

33:42.063 --> 33:43.195
HURRY, MATT!

33:49.679 --> 33:51.333
-MATT, SWIM! HURRY UP!

33:58.601 --> 34:00.255
-COME ON, MATT!

34:08.219 --> 34:09.830
MATT, ARE YOU OKAY?

34:10.396 --> 34:11.397
ARE YOU OKAY?

34:11.962 --> 34:14.007
MATT, YOU SAVED ME FROM A SHARK.

34:14.922 --> 34:16.271
-PINCH ME.
-WHY?

34:17.489 --> 34:19.143
-I WANT TO KNOW
IF THIS IS A DREAM.

34:19.840 --> 34:23.103
OW, I GUESS THIS IS A REAL ONE.

34:29.893 --> 34:32.025
-MATTIE: WHAT ARE
YOU DOING HERE, GWEN?

34:32.505 --> 34:35.072
-GWEN: MATTIE, WHERE IS MITCH?

34:35.856 --> 34:37.248
WHAT HAVE YOU DONE WITH HIM?

34:37.379 --> 34:39.554
-MITCH: I'M IN THE BASEMENT!
HELP ME! HELP ME!

34:39.686 --> 34:41.688
-GWEN: I'M GOING INTO
THE BASEMENT, MATTIE,

34:41.818 --> 34:42.906
AND YOU CANNOT STOP ME.

34:44.473 --> 34:46.954
-MATTIE: ARE YOU GONNA TRY
AND SAVE HIM FROM DROWNING?

34:48.042 --> 34:50.871
YOU ARE SO USELESS!

34:52.090 --> 34:54.396
YOU CAN'T SAVE ANYONE, GWEN.

34:55.789 --> 34:57.138
REMEMBER WHAT HAPPENED
THE LAST TIME YOU TRIED

34:57.269 --> 34:59.271
TO SAVE SOMEONE FROM DROWNING?

35:00.794 --> 35:02.012
-GWEN: SHUT UP!
SHUT UP! SHUT UP!

35:02.143 --> 35:03.536
IT WASN'T MY FAULT.

35:04.798 --> 35:05.712
I TRIED.

35:12.110 --> 35:13.763
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

35:13.894 --> 35:15.722
-YOU GOTTA GET ME OUT OF HERE!
THE TIDE'S COMING IN.

35:16.375 --> 35:18.551
I'LL DROWN. GET ME OUT
OF THESE HANDCUFFS!

35:18.681 --> 35:21.119
-GWEN WOULD LET
YOU DROWN, NOT ME.

35:22.555 --> 35:24.557
I'M A VICTIM TOO, MITCH.

35:25.079 --> 35:26.907
ALL OF THIS IS BECAUSE OF HER.

35:29.475 --> 35:31.303
[REVELATORY ORCHESTRAL MUSIC]

35:38.658 --> 35:39.485
-GWEN?

35:40.225 --> 35:42.009
-GWEN ISN'T HERE!

35:42.749 --> 35:45.491
FORGET ABOUT HER!
FORGET ABOUT GWEN.

35:45.621 --> 35:47.406
-I WANT TO TALK TO GWEN!
WHERE IS SHE?

35:48.624 --> 35:50.844
-GWEN CAN'T TAKE CARE OF YOU.

35:50.974 --> 35:52.672
GWEN CAN'T EVEN TAKE
CARE OF HERSELF!

35:55.675 --> 35:56.806
-WHO DID GWEN TRY TO SAVE?

35:56.937 --> 35:58.852
-I THOUGHT YOU CARED ABOUT ME.

35:59.505 --> 36:00.506
NOT GWEN.

36:00.636 --> 36:01.855
-I CARE ABOUT GWEN!

36:01.985 --> 36:03.770
WHO COULDN'T SHE SAVE?

36:04.858 --> 36:06.555
WHO COULDN'T GWEN SAVE, MATTIE?

36:09.384 --> 36:12.344
[DREAMLIKE MUSIC]

36:29.056 --> 36:30.318
WHO COULDN'T SHE SAVE?

36:30.449 --> 36:31.885
-GIRL'S VOICE: MATTIE.

36:33.582 --> 36:35.062
MATTIE?

36:38.021 --> 36:38.979
-GWEN.

36:39.109 --> 36:40.328
-MATTIE.

36:40.459 --> 36:42.678
-GWEN!
-MATTIE!

36:43.723 --> 36:44.724
MATTIE!

36:45.942 --> 36:48.641
-GUINEVERE, HELP ME!

36:50.295 --> 36:51.861
-WHO COULDN'T
GWEN SAVE, MATTIE?

36:51.992 --> 36:56.388
-NO, NO, NO, NO.

36:56.518 --> 36:57.780
-GUINEVERE.

36:59.739 --> 37:00.653
GUINEVERE, MY LADY.

37:03.873 --> 37:05.005
-MITCH.

37:07.050 --> 37:08.443
-HI.

37:09.879 --> 37:10.967
-OH, MY GOD.

37:13.753 --> 37:14.754
MITCH.

37:18.932 --> 37:20.455
ARE YOU OKAY?

37:20.586 --> 37:24.372
-YOU CAN HELP ME.
I'VE GOT HANDCUFFS ON HERE.

37:25.025 --> 37:29.986
THERE'S A KEY,
AND IT'S GOTTA BE IN A POCKET.

37:30.117 --> 37:31.292
MATTIE PROBABLY
PUT IT IN A POCKET.

37:32.119 --> 37:33.642
CHECK YOUR POCKETS.

37:33.773 --> 37:36.776
-MAMA, I TRIED TO
SAVE MATTIE, I TRIED.

37:39.909 --> 37:41.215
-GUINEVERE.

37:41.346 --> 37:45.132
-[SOBBING] I TRIED TO SAVE HER.

37:45.828 --> 37:48.875
-YOU COULDN'T SAVE HER,
BUT YOU CAN SAVE ME.

37:49.528 --> 37:51.573
COME ON, YOU CAN DO IT.

37:53.488 --> 37:57.100
LOOK IN YOUR POCKETS.
COME ON, MY LADY.

37:59.146 --> 38:00.800
COME ON, COME ON.

38:01.888 --> 38:03.411
YEAH, COME ON. COME ON.

38:03.542 --> 38:05.544
YEAH, GIVE IT TO ME.

38:06.545 --> 38:08.634
COME ON, GIVE THEM TO ME.
COME ON, GWEN.

38:10.026 --> 38:13.813
[FRANTIC SYNTH MUSIC]

38:30.264 --> 38:31.831
-MITCH, I TRIED TO SAVE HER.

38:31.961 --> 38:34.573
I TRIED TO SAVE HER,
DO YOU UNDERSTAND? I TRIED.

38:34.703 --> 38:36.226
-IT'S ALL RIGHT.
-I TRIED!

38:36.357 --> 38:37.619
[SOBBING] I TRIED TO SAVE HER!
-I UNDERSTAND.

38:37.750 --> 38:39.186
IT'S ALL RIGHT,
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

38:40.535 --> 38:43.233
MATTIE'S DEAD,
IT WASN'T YOUR FAULT.

38:44.800 --> 38:46.846
LOOK AT ME, YOU SAVED ME.

38:46.976 --> 38:48.108
YOU SAVED ME.

38:49.065 --> 38:50.415
YOU'VE GOT TO LET MATTIE GO.

38:51.720 --> 38:55.898
YOU'VE GOT TO LET HER GO.
YOU'VE GOT TO LET HER GO.

39:21.620 --> 39:25.188
-OH, MY GOD, NO, NO.
-IT'S OKAY, IT'S OKAY.

39:26.973 --> 39:28.235
GWEN, IT'S OKAY.

39:29.279 --> 39:30.977
THEY'RE GONNA GIVE YOU
THE HELP YOU NEED.

39:47.689 --> 39:49.343
YOU KNOW, YOU SAVED MY LIFE.

39:51.040 --> 39:53.303
-MATTIE WAS
EVERYTHING TO MY MAMA.

39:53.869 --> 39:55.784
I HAD TO KEEP HER ALIVE.

39:55.915 --> 39:57.307
-IT WASN'T YOUR FAULT.

39:58.396 --> 40:00.398
HER DEATH WAS AN ACCIDENT.

40:01.834 --> 40:04.358
-I GUESS I NEED TO
START BELIEVING THAT.

40:10.669 --> 40:13.193
WHEN I GET WELL,
CAN I COME AND SEE YOU?

40:15.543 --> 40:17.023
-YOU'D BETTER.

40:19.547 --> 40:20.635
-WOMAN: COME ON NOW.

40:22.855 --> 40:24.204
-IT'S OKAY.

40:44.790 --> 40:46.313
-EXCUSE ME, GENTLEMEN.

40:48.141 --> 40:50.491
WOULD YOU MIND TURNING
ON THE RADIO, PLEASE?

40:51.405 --> 40:53.929
-DRIVER: WHAT?
RADIO? NO PROBLEM.

40:56.715 --> 41:00.327
[SMOOTH JAZZ MUSIC]

41:13.209 --> 41:15.690
-I JUST LOVE TO DANCE.

41:17.475 --> 41:18.824
HOW ABOUT YOU FELLAS?

41:21.870 --> 41:25.787
[DEVIOUS LAUGHTER]

41:33.665 --> 41:36.494
[ENDING THEME PLAYS]
